body:
Release 6.1.0
--------------------------------------
- Added 1228800 and 2000000 baud rates to CH34xx driver.
- Microchip pid/vid correclty determined.
- FTDI sync method back to previous implementation.
- setBreak method implemented in CP210x devices.
- Added chunked stream methods.

name: UsbSerial
body: - Added  UC-232A Serial Port from ATEN manufacturer

name: UsbSerial
body:
- Added an example using the synchronous api.
- Solved a bug in syncRead method when a FTDI device is connected and timeout is set to 0.

name: UsbSerial
body:
- Solved some minor issues.
- Added a method "isSupported" to know wether a device is supported or not in a easier way.

name: UsbSerial
body: CH340 new driver implemented with more baud rates, RTS/CTD, DTR/DSR and Parity

name: UsbSerial 4.1
body: Added synchronous write and read operations

name: UsbSerial 4.0
body: RTS/CTS and DTR/DSR flow control signals added for CP210x and FTDI devices.

name: UsbSerial 3.2
body: Updated jar file with the safeguards to null callbacks

name: UsbSerial 2.3
body: Added support for CH34x which are present in some Arduino clones.

name: UsbSerial 2.2
body: Added support for multi interface devices
